friend finish the wonderful quest known as J-boots. Unfortunalty an &quot;uber&quot; guild twink druid decided that she needed the camp more then we did- and proceeded to nuke every mob we engaged. We won a few but were begining to lose ground as she became more aggressive with her tatics. Looking through my various bags of loot I noticed a nice little tidbit I picked up off of Thistle the brownine in Lesser Faydark- mistletoe powder. For those of you who don't know what it is- it has one charge of Befriend animal, and thats what I did. Went out and befriended me the biggiest Kodiak I could find. Then I told my new found friend to have a seat while I chatted with the lady. Unfortunatly the druid felt the tag after her name gave her free reign to cause chaos throughout the land, and that being my job I convinced her to type /duel while targeting my name.....*evil grin*.<br>
As most hot headed casters who are quick to duel learn, he who types /d first is now on the waiting game for the other to accept. I snuck/hid and manuvered around her for a while- making her nervous... then resumed pulling the camp to the taunts in shout of &quot;Punk @$$ rogues who never have any b@ll$&quot;. Then the moment of decision. The spell was close to ending on the kodiak so I told my partner to hold off on attacking at all. I aggroed the entire pop of 5 shadow men at the same time *most being necro casters*, and at her first aoe nuke- jammed on the evade key- all ran right at her. My hand slipped and i accidently targeted her and hit /d <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  . Then a strange occourance- I said the magic /pet attack and my kodiak friend started whomping on her. Mind melt dripping from my blade, I quickly circled and after the initial backstab- poisioned her- removing a majority of her mana. Now out of spells- and melee skills painfully inadequate from quad kiting reds from a distance for most of her 48 seasons... she quickly dropped to the combined onslaught of our attacks. The druid removed from my sights, and the ensuing aggro cleared, my cleric friend could do nothing but proclaim that he would never allow himself to cross a rogue....... and the warning was issued to all that would dare think of doing so- Rogues live not because of armor- not because of damage- Rogues live because they are rogues... and always have an option. Fight well all, and always remember we are the best because we always have options. <p>"Do you know how to use that thing? Yes, The pointy end goes in the other  man..."Graynd Theftauto <BR> *redeemed rogue*
